I’m one of the CADD/Build mentors who was closely monitoring this part. The (4) of the (8) 8-32 FHCS were accessible from the end. the other (4) we planned to create access holes but never populated. If we had issues we would have needed to remove the 1x2 then the TieFigher. The Motors were attached to the TieFigher.

image793×621 56.4 KB

I should also add that we never had any issues with the Krackens. CTRE and WCP created a very reliable product from day Zero, in our opinion. We are excited to see what accessories are developed to bolt on and extend the capabilities in 2025.
